verbose_text: We have no actual reasonably (age-, sex- and referral pattern-) matched reference cohort available; however, it is noteworthy that the mean 25-OH vitamin D levels in our PH patients were almost identical to those found in elderly (age 65+, mean> 80years) patients admitted from home (from a comparable referral area, over the same time period, assessed with the same 25-OH vitamin D assay) to the hospital for hip fracture, considered severely vitamin D deficient [XREF_BIBR].
